    <text>
        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)"> <persName role="author">Rev. D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>.Eckman</persName> at
                    <placeName>Augusta</placeName></p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Augusta</placeName><date>Augusta March 30<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                    1852</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">You will please insert the following<lb/> once in your periodical.&#8212;&#8212; </p>
            <p><add>In left margin&#58; Long Primo</add> &#8220;At a meeting of the Board of Managers of the
                Congregation &#8220;B&#39;nai&#8211;<lb/>Israel&#8221; of <placeName>Augusta
                    Ga</placeName>&#44; on <date>February 23&#44; 1852</date>&#40; The following
                preamble<lb/> and resolution were unanimously passed&#8212;&#8220;Whereas the<lb/>
                <persName>Rev. Dr Julius Eckman</persName> having accepted the special invitation of
                this<lb/> congregation&#44; and delivered a series of Lectures long to be
                remembered<lb/> with feelings of admiration&#8212;and whereas this congregation
                have<lb/> found in the <persName>Rev. Dr.</persName> a truly pious man&#8212;a profound scholar and
                a<lb/> gentleman........./</p>
            <p>Resolved&#8212;That a proper and suitable token expressive of our feelings be
                purchased&#8212;<lb/>&#8212;&#8211;A <sic>committy</sic> being appointed for <del>that</del>
                its selection&#8212;they reported<lb/> at a meeting of the Congregation on the
                        <date>28<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Feby</date>. that <persName>Lewis
                    Levy</persName> and<lb/>
                <persName>Samuel Levy Esqrs</persName>  had purchased a silver Goblet&#44; as
                directed&#44; and that<lb/> this Goblet and the sum of Fifty Dollars be presented to
                the Rev gentleman<lb/> the <sic>Committy</sic> further reported&#44; that they had
                selected <persName>Henry Morrison Esqr</persName> <lb/> to present the same....At a
                meeting of the Congregation on <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March</date>&#44; it
                was/</p>
            <p>Resolved. That a <sic>committy</sic> be appointed to return the thanks of this
                congregation to<lb/>
                <persName>H. Morrison Esqr.</persName>  for his able address delivered at the
                Presentation&#59; and that<lb/>
                <persName>H. Morrison Esqr&#44;</persName>  and the <persName>Rev. Dr.
                    Eckman</persName> be respectfully requested to furnish<lb/> the
                    <sic>Committy</sic> with a copy of their respective addresses.</p>
            <p>Resolved That the whole of these proceedings be published in the Asmonean and<lb/>
                Occident.....<lb/> <add>In left margin&#58; Small Pica</add> After the <persName> Rev. Dr.
                    Eckman</persName> had delivered his last lecture&#44; on<lb/> Sunday
                    <date>March 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> <persName>Mr Morrison</persName>
                arose and addressed him as follows.&#8212;&#8211; </p>


        </body>
